snippet.textDisplay:
According to Rachel Maddow, Trump is a Russian puppet who does what Putin tells him to.
So Putin just convinced Trump to murder an Iranian commander who was a close Russian ally in the fight against ISIS. Previously, Putin convinced Trump to send sophisticated weapons to a Ukrainian military that includes an openly neo-Nazi, Russophobic, battalion. Putin also convinced his ''puppet'' in Washington to place swingeing sanctions on Russian goods and individuals too. Putin also convinced his lackey, Donald Trump, to protect ISIS and Al Qaeda and Al Nusra and other head choppers in Syria which the Russian military was fighting at the time.
Now I'm no Bertrand Russell but I don't think both those positions can be logically held at the same time. Either Iran and Russia weren't allies in the fight against ISIS (but they clearly were). Or Trump is not a puppet of Putin (and he clearly never was). But the stocks of Raytheon Boeing and other weapons manufacturers shot up after the assassination. War pays. And war crimes pay too. Ask Maddow, I'm sure she has shares in Boeing and Raytheon herself.
